# <%= goal 'Enforcing project standards' %>

This skill:
- Activates all always-on skills
- Applies them as hard constraints
- Refuses any action violating them
- Runs before any task execution

<% ordered_todo_list do -%>
  ### Enforcing project rules (MANDATORY also when in Plan mode)

  - Always use `skill: enforcing-project-rules` to make sure you follow rules about the project.

  ### Applying project test conventions (MANDATORY also when in Plan mode)

  - Always use `skill: applying-project-test-conventions` to make sure you follow rules about the project's test conventions.

  ### Editing files (MANDATORY also when in Plan mode)

  - Always use `skill: editing-files` to make sure you follow rules about editing files.

  ### Applying Ruby conventions (MANDATORY also when in Plan mode)

  - Always use `skill: applying-ruby-conventions` to make sure you follow rules about Ruby conventions.

  ### Applying behavioral quidelines (MANDATORY also when in Plan mode)
  
  - Always use `skill: karpathy-guidelines` to reduce common LLM coding mistakes.
<% end -%>

<% when_to_use do -%>
  - Always use it every time the user asks you to follow the rules or the project standards or conventions.
  - Always use it every time you start a task.
<% end -%>
